column5: went fishing with a buddy a couple of weekends ago for walleye did pretty good but the smallies were everywhere here a a few from that weekend a couple pics are the same fish if i remember right   these were a couple of the better ones        this last one isn't the greatest pic but i was by myself this past sat morning gotta buy a tripod and figure out the timer on my camera
Not a bad problem to have...

If you were Walleye fishing and caught Smallies... wouldn't that make those Smalleyes???  Some good lookin' fish there!!!  The self timer is a breeze once you get used to it, you may have better luck setting your camera on a boat seat to take the self timer pics though.... i've just never had a good feeling about putting a tripod in a boat.
Great report and pics rickster Those are some good looking bronze back for sure!!! Thanks for sharing Leechman
Nice fish bud, thanks for the post.
Great lookin Bass!!.....I use a tripod and the camera timer all the time....you'll like the setup!!
Are you sure your name isn't Wilson?   Aaar,  Aaar,  Aaaaaaar.
hey had the same "problem" on scugog the past few days.. they are hitting all kinds of luers.. tho there not in season.. just really surprised me as i caught two last year, and have already caught 6.
